
exif2map.pl v2012.05.24
Perl script to take the output of exiftool and conjure up a web link
to google maps if the image has stored GPS lat/long info.

Usage: exif2map.pl [-h|help] [-f filename] [-html]
-h|help .......... Help (print this information). Does not run anything else.
-f filename ...... File(s) to extract lat/long from
-dir directory ... Absolute/Relative path to folder containing file(s) to extract lat/long from
-html ............ Also output results as a timestamped html file in current directory

Example: exif2map.pl -f /cases/galloping-gonzo.jpg -f /cases/krazy-kermit.jpg
Example: exif2map.pl -f /cases/krazy-kermit.jpg -dir /cases/rockin-rowlf-pics/ -html

Note: Outputs results to command line and (if specified) to a timestamped html file
in the current directory (e.g. exif2map-output-TIMESTAMP.html)

